<Class name="CM_YABlockGroup" id="6d90f3fc-8b8f-4d46-afe5-06f019647477">
    <superclass name="CM_YAEntity"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>There will always be at least one (default) Group Block for an allocation, however
if the Terminal Config option to use grouped blocks is not set, then the default
group will be hidden from the user, and they will not be able to maintain Group Blocks.

There is a method on the CM_YardAllocation class (isGroupedBlocks) which indicates
whether blocks are grouped.</text>
